fields.name: Adult & Babies
fields.description: Age 6 to 18 months - Introduction to the aquatic environment supported by their parent/guardian in the water.

fields.name: Adult & Toddlers
fields.description: Age 19 to 36 months - Becoming independent swimming alongside parent/guardian.

fields.name: Splash
fields.description: Age 3 upwards - Developing confidence in aquatic independence

fields.name: Level 1
fields.description: Age 5 upwards - Introduction to a structured learning environment

fields.name: Level 2
fields.description: Age 5 upwards - Developing the foundations of all strokes – buoyancy and balance

fields.name: Level 3
fields.description: Age 6 upwards - Developing propulsion from leg kick while introducing arm pull

fields.name: Level 4
fields.description: Age 6 upwards - Developing the stroke mastering arm pull

fields.name: Level 5
fields.description: Age 7 upwards - Introduction to deep water and swimming lengths

fields.name: Level 6
fields.description: Age 7 upwards - Developing stamina and endurance while maintaining stroke technique

fields.name: Level 7
fields.description: Age 8 upwards - Longer sessions introducing set training

fields.name: Level 8
fields.description: Age 8 upwards - Introduction to multi aquatic disciplines

fields.name: Rookie Lifeguard
fields.description: Age 8 upwards - Starting your Lifesaving journey, learn survival skills and basic land-based rescue techniques

fields.name: Survive & Save
fields.description: Age 12 upwards - Developing Lifesaving skills, through Bronze, Silver and Gold awards, in pool and open water.

fields.name: Lifeguards
fields.description: Age 16 upwards - Obtain a professional National Pool Lifeguard Qualification
